   {
      "body" : "@sipa printf needs to use a lock to ensure multiple threads aren't writing at the same time, but signals can interrupt writes (while that lock is held). If this happens, the printf in the signal handler will try to lock again, and block. Even if the lock is recursive, there is a risk of the signal printf mixing output with the ongoing one.",
      "created_at" : "2012-05-18T20:05:20Z",
      "html_url" : "https://github.com/bitcoin/bitcoin/pull/1305#issuecomment-5794391",
